display="inline"><![CDATA[r \colon  A \to  B]]></fr:tex> be a pair of maps. A homotopy <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[h \colon  r\circ  s \sim  1_{B}]]></fr:tex> exhibits <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex> as a <fr:em><fr:strong>section</fr:strong></fr:em> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[r]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[r]]></fr:tex> as a <fr:em><fr:strong>retraction</fr:strong></fr:em> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex>. Together, 
 <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left \lparen s,r\right \rparen \mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>
 are referred to as a <fr:em><fr:strong>section-retraction pair</fr:strong></fr:em>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
